  <brief_title>Cross-linking of Corneal Collagen (CXL) With Ultraviolet-A in Asymmetric Corneas</brief_title>
  <official_title>Collagen Crosslinking With Ultraviolet-A in Asymmetric Corneas</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Cxlusa</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Cxlusa</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to evaluate the efficacy of ultraviolet-A (UVA)-induced
      cross-linking of corneal collagen (CXL) as a method to increase the biomechanical and
      biochemical stability of the cornea by inducing additional cross-links within or between
      collagen fibers using UVA light and the photo- mediator riboflavin. The purpose of this study
      is to generate data for presentation at medical meetings and for peer-review publication. The
      data generated by this study will not be submitted to the FDA to support commercialization of
      these riboflavin drops.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
